BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
The following three points are given in polar coordinates.  What are the Cartesian coordinates of each point?

$PAR$HR$PAR
(a) \((3,\pi/2)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR$HR$PAR
(b) \((2\sqrt{2},3\pi/4)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR$HR$PAR
(c) \((-1,\pi/3)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("0"));
ANS(num_cmp("3"));
ANS(num_cmp("-2"));
ANS(num_cmp("2"));
ANS(num_cmp("-1/2"));
ANS(num_cmp("-1*sqrt(3)/2"));

